  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read the auth pattern + ADR-028 + DocumentRelationshipViewer's three auth files end-to-end.</step>
    <step order="2">Verify `@spaarke/auth` is in `package.json` deps; add if missing (same version as DocumentRelationshipViewer).</step>
    <step order="3">Create `src/services/auth/MsalAuthProvider.ts` (or `src/auth/MsalAuthProvider.ts` matching scaffold location from task 030) — copy from exemplar, adapt only as needed for EmailComposer scope.</step>
    <step order="4">Create `src/services/auth/msalConfig.ts` — copy from exemplar (scopes, authority, cache config should match unless email scope diverges, which it should NOT for this composer surface).</step>
    <step order="5">Create `src/services/authInit.ts` — copy from exemplar; the auth-init entry point called by `index.tsx`.</step>
    <step order="6">Update `src/index.tsx` — call `authInit()` before rendering `<App />`; await silent acquisition; only then mount React root (mirror exemplar's pattern).</step>
    <step order="7">Update `src/App.tsx` — wrap App body with the auth provider component; expose `authenticatedFetch` via a React Context so child components (later, task 033's `<SendEmailPage />`) can consume it via prop pass-through.</step>
    <step order="8">Create or update a small `AuthContext.tsx` (or place context in MsalAuthProvider.ts) exposing `{ authenticatedFetch, account, isAuthenticated }`.</step>
    <step order="9">Run `npm run build`; confirm clean build.</step>
    <step order="9.5">QUALITY GATE — Run `code-review` skill on the auth-related files; run `adr-check` against ADR-028 + NFR-02. Confirm: (a) no `@spaarke/auth` import outside Code Page; (b) silent bootstrap path correct; (c) error handling for token-acquisition failure present.</step>
    <step order="10">Local smoke: temporarily add a debug `console.log` near `authenticatedFetch` to confirm it's defined when App mounts. Remove debug log before completion.</step>
    <step order="11">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 031 ✅ completed.</step>
    <step order="12">Update `current-task.md` per task-execute protocol: status → completed; advance to next pending task (032).</step>
  </steps>

